T1  - Foreign exchange rates: A multiple currency and maturity analysis
AU  - Havenner, Arthur
AU  - Modjtahedi, Bagher
JO  - Journal of Econometrics
VL  - 37
IS  - 2
SP  - 251
EP  - 264
PY  - 1988
DA  - 1988/02/01/
SN  - 0304-4076
DO  - https://doi.org/10.1016/0304-4076(88)90005-X
UR  - https://www.sciencedirect.com/science/article/pii/030440768890005X
AB  - Three dollar exchange-rate series — the German mark, the British pound, and the Japanese yen — are converted to market price revisions by calculating the difference between the price for delivery at a fixed date and the preceding period's price for delivery at the same date. These price revisions are likely to meet the stationary stochastic process assumptions required for time-series modeling even if the original series are non-stationary. Using error covariance assumptions analogous to a pooled time series of cross-sections, a multivariate time-series model is fitted and tested on 168 observations out of sample. Forecasting performance is evaluated using both mean squared errors and a non-parametric test of direction.
ER  - 

